        "20003": {
            "id": "20003",
            "marks": 3,
            "negative_marks": 1.0,
            "is_input_type": false,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "A man travels from city A to city B at speed of 45 km/hr and returns back from city B to city A at a certain speed. If his average speed for the entire journey is 90km/hr, then find his return speed? 1 &nbsp;",
            "options": [
                "km/hr",
                "km/hr",
                "km/hr",
                "Data inconsistent"
            ],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "4"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution: <br>Correct Answer : <b>4</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div><b>In a to and fro motion, the average speed can never be double or\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tmore than double of one of the speeds.</div></div>"
        },
        "20004": {
            "id": "20004",
            "marks": 3,
            "negative_marks": 0.0,
            "is_input_type": true,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "If N<sup>2</sup> ends with 76, where N is a natural number less than or equals to 350, then how many such N are possible? <ul class='list-group'> <li class='list-group-item'><B><a href='#quesSol1576351' data-toggle='collapse' aria-expanded='true'> Answer key/Solution</a></B></li> </ul>",
            "options": [],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "14"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<br>Correct Answer : <b>14</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div><b>Last two digits of perfect squares keeps on repeating after 25 in\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tgroup of every 25 numbers.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNow, in first 25 natural numbers, there is only one number whose\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tsquare ends with 76.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSo, there are 14 such numbers till 350, as we get 14 groups of 25\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tnumbers.</div></div>"
        },
