            "is_input_type": false,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "While buying rice, Neerav made profit using a faulty balance of 1200 grams instead of 1000 grams. While selling them, he further marked up the price by 20% and then offered a discount of 25%. Find the net profit /loss of Neerav on the whole transaction. 1 &nbsp;",
            "options": [
                "% loss",
                ".5% profit",
                "% profit",
                "% loss"
            ],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "3"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution: <br>Correct\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAnswer : <b>3</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div><img src=https://clsite-file.s3.amazonaws.com/LSTQuestionImg/773323/842833/71s.gif>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div></div>"
        },
        "20009": {
            "id": "20009",
            "marks": 3,
            "negative_marks": 0.0,
            "is_input_type": true,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "Raju can finish a job in 20 days and Monu is half as efficient as Raju. Raju worked for \u2018x\u2019 days alone and then left the job. After that Monu started working on it. But after y days, Raju joined him and they together took 7 more days to finish the work. For maximum how many days did Monu work alone?(x, y are natural numbers) <ul class='list-group'> <li class='list-group-item'><B><a href='#quesSol1576337' data-toggle='collapse' aria-expanded='true'> Answer key/Solution</a></B></li> </ul>",
            "options": [],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "17"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution: <br>Correct\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAnswer : <b>17</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div>Since Raju can finish in 20 days, Monu will take 40 days to finish the same work.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tLet the amount of work be LCM (20, 40) = 40 units<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tRaju can do 2 units/day and Monu can do 1 unit/day.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSo, 2x + y + 3 \u00d7 7 = 40<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u21d2 2x + y = 19<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u21d2 y = 19 \u2013 2x<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u21d2 maximum (y) = 19 \u2013 2 \u00d7 1 = 17 (minimum (x) = 1, as x and y are natural numbers)</div></div>"
        },
